1) Jump Game (LC 55)
Problem

Given an array nums, each element tells the maximum jump length from that position.

Return true if you can reach the last index.

Example
nums = [2,3,1,1,4]

0 → jump 1 step
1 → jump 3 steps
Reach end

Output: true
Greedy Idea

Track the farthest index reachable.

If current index becomes greater than farthest → impossible.

Dry Run
nums=[2,3,1,1,4]

i=0 far=2
i=1 far=max(2,1+3)=4
i=2 far=4
Reached end

Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)
2) Jump Game II (LC 45)
Problem

Return the minimum jumps needed to reach last index.

Example
nums=[2,3,1,1,4]

0 → 1 → 4

Answer = 2
Greedy Idea

Treat reachable positions like levels.

Maintain:

far → farthest reachable
end → current jump boundary
jump → count

When index reaches end, make another jump.

Dry Run
nums=[2,3,1,1,4]

i=0
far=2
end=0 → jump=1

i=1
far=4

i=2
end=2 → jump=2


Complexity
Time: O(n)
Space: O(1)
